# Development Workflow

This project uses a `Makefile` to streamline common development tasks. Below are some useful commands:

- **Formatting and Linting**
    - `make format`: Formats code using `trunk fmt`. (Refer to [Makefile](mdc:Makefile))
    - `make format-all`: Formats all code using `trunk fmt -a`. (Refer to [Makefile](mdc:Makefile))
    - `make lint`: Lints code using `trunk check`. This also runs `make format` first. (Refer to [Makefile](mdc:Makefile))
    - `make lint-all`: Lints all code using `trunk check -a`. This also runs `make format-all` first. (Refer to [Makefile](mdc:Makefile))

- **Testing**
    - `make test`: Runs unit tests. (Refer to [Makefile](mdc:Makefile))
    - `make coverage`: Runs unit tests and generates a coverage report. (Refer to [Makefile](mdc:Makefile))

- **Building and Running**
    - `make build`: Builds the main application binary. (Refer to [Makefile](mdc:Makefile))
    - `make run`: Builds and runs the application. (Refer to [Makefile](mdc:Makefile))
    - `make dev`: Runs the application with live reload using `air`. (Refer to [Makefile](mdc:Makefile))

- **Dependencies**
    - `make deps`: Downloads Go module dependencies and tidies the `go.mod` file. (Refer to [Makefile](mdc:Makefile))
